thread.title: Blair Oaks takes volleyball title

author: News Tribune
title: Blair Oaks takes volleyball title
text:
VERSAILLES, Mo. — The Blair Oaks Lady Falcons went 6-0 on Saturday to capture the title at the Versailles Tournament. 
Blair Oaks defeated California 25-13, 25-13 in the title match. 
Sadie Turner had 11 assists, while Jayde Peters finished with six aces. Rebecca Schroeder totaled 10 digs. Ryan Dudenhoeffer had six kills and four blocks. Allison Maxwell, Taylor Stockman, Alexa Stegemann and Paige Rackers all added four kills. 
Blair Oaks posted another 25-13, 25-13 win in the semifinals, this one against Eldon. 
Dudenhoeffer and Rackers both had five kills. Dudenhoeffer also had four aces and three blocks. Maxwell and Stegemann both had four kills. 
In the first match of tournament play, Blair Oaks topped School of the Osage 25-11, 25-6. 
Rackers and Maxwell had five kills each, while Maxwell also had two blocks. Turner totaled 11 assists and seven aces, while Schroeder had eight digs. 
Blair Oaks defeated Osage (25-12, 25-20), Southern Boone (25-17, 25-6) and Fulton (25-20, 25-14) in pool play. 
Turner finished with 21 assists and 11 aces in pool play, while Schroeder had 17 digs and Stegemann had 12. Stockman led with 11 kills and Maxwell had 10. 
Blair Oaks (29-3-2) will wrap up Tri-County Conference play Tuesday against Versailles. The Lady Falcons have already won the conference title. ﻿
